.TH JIGSAW 1 "February 2026" "jigsaw 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jigsaw \- intelligent password wordlist generator for offensive security
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jigsaw
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B jigsaw
\fBserver\fR [\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B JIGSAW
(Joint Intelligence Generator for Strategic Attack Wordlists) is a
high\-performance, Rust\-based intelligent wordlist generator designed for
modern offensive security. It employs probabilistic models, targeted
personal profiling, and advanced permutation logic to generate high\-value
password candidates.
.SH MODES
.SS "Mask Attack"
Generate password candidates from a Hashcat\-style mask pattern.
.PP
.B jigsaw \-m
\fIMASK\fR [\fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR]
.PP
Charset tokens: \fB?l\fR (lowercase), \fB?u\fR (uppercase), \fB?d\fR (digits),
\fB?s\fR (special), \fB?a\fR (all). Literal characters are used as\-is.
.SS "Markov Chain"
Train a probabilistic model on an existing wordlist, then generate
similar password candidates.
.PP
.B jigsaw \-\-train
\fIWORDLIST\fR [\fB\-\-model\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.br
.B jigsaw \-\-markov \-\-model
\fIPATH\fR [\fB\-\-count\fR \fIN\fR]
.SS "Personal Attack"
Generate a targeted wordlist using a JSON profile containing names,
dates, companies, cities, and other personal information.
.PP
.B jigsaw \-\-personal \-\-profile
\fIPATH\fR [\fB\-\-level\fR \fILEVEL\fR]
.PP
Levels: \fBquick\fR, \fBstandard\fR (default), \fBdeep\fR, \fBinsane\fR.
.SS "Memorable Passwords"
Generate human\-memorable yet strong passwords.
.PP
.B jigsaw \-\-memorable
[\fB\-\-words\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-\-mem\-style\fR \fISTYLE\fR] [\fB\-\-mem\-count\fR \fIN\fR]
.PP
Styles: \fBclassic\fR (Adjective\-Noun\-Verb), \fBpassphrase\fR (random word chain),
\fBstory\fR (subject\-verb\-object), \fBalliterative\fR (same starting letter).
.SS "REST API Server"
Start an HTTP API server exposing JIGSAW functionality.
.PP
.B jigsaw server
[\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR]
.SS "Interactive Wizard"
A guided, step\-by\-step interactive CLI for building profiles and
selecting modes.
.PP
.B jigsaw \-\-interactive
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write output to FILE instead of stdout.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: \fBplain\fR (default) or \fBjson\fR.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-threads " " \fIN\fR
Number of threads (default: automatic based on CPU cores).
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Run the interactive wizard mode.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mask " " \fIMASK\fR
Mask pattern for mask attack mode.
.TP
.BR \-\-train " " \fIWORDLIST\fR
Train a Markov model from the given wordlist file.
.TP
.BR \-\-model " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to Markov model file (default: jigsaw.model).
.TP
.BR \-\-markov
Run in Markov generation mode using a trained model.
.TP
.BR \-\-count " " \fIN\fR
Number of candidates to generate in Markov mode (default: 10000).
.TP
.BR \-\-personal
Enable Personal Attack mode.
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to a Personal Profile JSON file.
.TP
.BR \-\-level " " \fILEVEL\fR
Generation intensity: quick, standard, deep, insane.
.TP
.BR \-\-min\-length " " \fIN\fR
Minimum password length filter.
.TP
.BR \-\-max\-length " " \fIN\fR
Maximum password length filter.
.TP
.BR \-\-check " " \fIPASSWORD\fR
Check if PASSWORD exists in the generated candidate list.
.TP
.BR \-\-memorable
Generate memorable password(s).
.TP
.BR \-\-words " " \fIN\fR
Number of words in memorable password (default: 3).
.TP
.BR \-\-mem\-sep " " \fISEP\fR
Separator between words in memorable password.
.TP
.BR \-\-mem\-style " " \fISTYLE\fR
Memorable password style: classic, passphrase, story, alliterative.
.TP
.BR \-\-mem\-case " " \fICASE\fR
Case style: title, lower, upper, random, alternating.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-number
Skip number in memorable password.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-special
Skip special character in memorable password.
.TP
.BR \-\-mem\-count " " \fIN\fR
How many memorable passwords to generate (default: 1).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate an 8\-character lowercase/numeric mask wordlist:
.PP
.RS
.B jigsaw \-m \(dq?l?l?l?l?d?d?d?d\(dq \-o wordlist.txt
.RE
.PP
Train a Markov model on a wordlist:
.PP
.RS
.B jigsaw \-\-train rockyou.txt \-\-model my.model
.RE
.PP
Generate Markov passwords:
.PP
.RS
.B jigsaw \-\-markov \-\-model my.model \-\-count 100000 \-o output.txt
.RE
.PP
Run a personal attack:
.PP
.RS
.B jigsaw \-\-personal \-\-profile target.json \-\-level deep \-o targeted.txt
.RE
.PP
Generate 5 memorable passwords:
.PP
.RS
.B jigsaw \-\-memorable \-\-mem\-count 5 \-\-mem\-style passphrase \-\-mem\-sep \(dq\-\(dq
.RE
.PP
Start the API server on port 9090:
.PP
.RS
.B jigsaw server \-\-port 9090
.RE
